1.How to compile a java file?
Ans:In CMD: Open CMD > GoTo directory containing your java program > Type "javac yourcode.java and press Enter"

2.How to run a class file?
Ans:A class file can be run in CMD while typing "java filename".

3.How to debug a java file?
Ans:Right click on the Java class file and select  Debug.

4.How to set Classpath?
Ans:i)Go to Advanced system settings in the control panel and then Go to Advanced system settings in the control panel.
	ii)Then by clicking on New, a New System Variable dialog will open in which you have enter variable name and variable value.
	iii)Then  click on OK, a Edit environment variable dialog will open and you will be able to set the path.
  
 5.How to view current classpath?
 Ans:Go to Advanced system settings in the control panel and then goto Advanced tab and click on Environment Variables.
	ii)In System variable, there is available current path.
  
 6.How to set the destination of class file?
 Ans:In order to set the destination of .class file we use -d option while compiling the ” .java” file.
 
 7.How to run a compiled class file?
 Ans:1. Go to the path where you saved the java file you want to compile.
    2.Replace path by typing cmd and press enter.
    3..Enter javac javafile.java and Press Enter. It will automatically generate java class file.
    
  8.How to check version of java running on your system?
  Ans:typing "java -version" in CMD.
  
  9.How to set classpath when class files are in .jar file?
Ans.	To set CLASSPATH environment variable, find the location of user environment variables in your machine and add all paths where Jar files are stored.
Use the separator between different two folders, jar files or classes.
